records.text: ## What is the device? The Signifier sleep therapy device is a tongue muscle stimulation system designed to reduce sleep apnea symptoms by strengthening upper airway muscles. It is not a CPAP and does not deliver airflow.
## How do I charge the device? Use the supplied USB-C cable. A full charge takes ~2 hours. The status LED turns solid green when fully charged.
## Cleaning and care Wipe the mouthpiece with a soft, damp cloth and mild soap. Do not submerge the control unit.
## Troubleshooting: no stimulation felt Ensure the mouthpiece is seated correctly, increase the intensity gradually, and verify the battery is charged. If the issue persists, contact support.
## Appointments and support For appointments, rescheduling, or device support, contact support@signifier.com or call +44 20 1234 5678.
